name: Baked Chicken Wings
briefdescription: These baked chicken wings are easy to prep with a spicy coating, then baked to crispy perfection for a delicious way to prepare chicken wings.

ingredients: salt and ground black pepper to taste

instructions: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).

Combine olive oil, garlic, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a large, resealable bag; seal and shake to combine. Add chicken wings; reseal and shake to coat. Arrange chicken wings on a baking sheet.
Cook chicken wings in the preheated oven until crisp and cooked through, about 1 hour.

comments.comment: The prep work is easy. I let my wings marinate overnight. While your wings are baking, make some celery sticks and get your favorite dip ready. These wings taste excellent.
